# Sura LXXVI.: Dahr, or Time, or Insān, or Man.

### Section 1

![](../gif/076/076_001.gif)

1. Hal at<u>a</u> AAal<u>a</u> al-ins<u>a</u>ni <u>h</u>eenun mina
a**l**ddahri lam yakun shay-an ma<u>th</u>koor<u>a</u>**n**

1\. Has there not been  
Over Man a long period  
Of Time, when he was  
Nothing—(not even) mentioned?

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/076/076_002.gif)

2. Inn<u>a</u> khalaqn<u>a</u> al-ins<u>a</u>na min nu<u>t</u>fatin
amsh<u>a</u>jin nabtaleehi fajaAAaln<u>a</u>hu sameeAAan
ba<u>s</u>eer<u>a</u>**n**

2\. Verily We created  
Man from a drop  
Of mingled sperm,  
In order to try him:  
So We gave him (the gifts).  
Of Hearing and Sight.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/076/076_003.gif)

3. Inn<u>a</u> hadayn<u>a</u>hu a**l**ssabeela imm<u>a</u>
sh<u>a</u>kiran wa-imm<u>a</u> kafoor<u>a</u>**n**

3\. We showed him, the Way:  
Whether he be grateful  
Or ungrateful (rests  
On his will).

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/076/076_004.gif)

4. Inn<u>a</u> aAAtadn<u>a</u> lilk<u>a</u>fireena sal<u>a</u>sila
waaghl<u>a</u>lan wasaAAeer<u>a</u>**n**

4\. For the Rejecters  
We have prepared  
Chains, Yokes, and  
A Blazing Fire.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/076/076_005.gif)

5. Inna al-abr<u>a</u>ra yashraboona min ka/sin k<u>a</u>na
miz<u>a</u>juh<u>a</u> k<u>a</u>foor<u>a</u>**n**

5\. As to the Righteous,  
They shall drink  
Of a Cup (of Wine)  
Mixed with Kāfūr,—

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/076/076_006.gif)

6. AAaynan yashrabu bih<u>a</u> AAib<u>a</u>du All<u>a</u>hi
yufajjiroonah<u>a</u> tafjeer<u>a</u>**n**

6\. A Fountain where  
The Devotees of God  
Do drink, making it  
Flow in unstinted abundance.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/076/076_007.gif)

7. Yoofoona bi**al**nna<u>th</u>ri wayakh<u>a</u>foona yawman
k<u>a</u>na sharruhu musta<u>t</u>eer<u>a</u>**n**

7\. They perform (their) vows,  
And they fear a Day  
Whose evil flies far and wide.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/076/076_008.gif)

8. Wayu<u>t</u>AAimona a**l**<u>tt</u>aAA<u>a</u>ma AAal<u>a</u>
<u>h</u>ubbihi miskeenan wayateeman waaseer<u>a</u>**n**

8\. And they feed, for the love  
Of God, the indigent,  
The orphan, and the captive,—

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/076/076_009.gif)

9. Innam<u>a</u> nu<u>t</u>AAimukum liwajhi All<u>a</u>hi l<u>a</u>
nureedu minkum jaz<u>a</u>an wal<u>a</u> shukoor<u>a</u>**n**

9\. (Saying), "We feed you  
For the sake of God alone:  
No reward do we desire  
From you, nor thanks.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/076/076_010.gif)

10. Inn<u>a</u> nakh<u>a</u>fu min rabbin<u>a</u> yawman AAaboosan
qam<u>t</u>areer<u>a</u>**n**

10\. "We only fear a Day  
Of distressful Wrath  
From the side of our Lord."

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/076/076_011.gif)

11. Fawaq<u>a</u>humu All<u>a</u>hu sharra <u>tha</u>lika alyawmi
walaqq<u>a</u>hum na<u>d</u>ratan wasuroor<u>a</u>**n**

11\. But God will deliver  
Them from the evil  
Of that Day, and will  
Shed over them a Light  
Of Beauty and  
A (blissful) Joy.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/076/076_012.gif)

12. Wajaz<u>a</u>hum bim<u>a</u> <u>s</u>abaroo jannatan
wa<u>h</u>areer<u>a</u>**n**

12\. And because they were  
Patient and constant, He will  
Reward them with a Garden  
And (garments of) silk.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/076/076_013.gif)

13. Muttaki-eena feeh<u>a</u> AAal<u>a</u> al-ar<u>a</u>-iki l<u>a</u>
yarawna feeh<u>a</u> shamsan wal<u>a</u> zamhareer<u>a</u>**n**

13\. Reclining in the (Garden)  
On raised thrones,  
They will see there neither  
The sun's (excessive heat)  
Nor (the moon's) excessive cold.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/076/076_014.gif)

14. Wad<u>a</u>niyatan AAalayhim *<u>th</u>*il<u>a</u>luh<u>a</u>
wa<u>th</u>ullilat qu<u>t</u>oofuh<u>a</u> ta<u>th</u>leel<u>a</u>**n**

14\. And the shades of the (Garden)  
Will come low over them,  
And the bunches (of fruit),  
There, will hang low  
In humility.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/076/076_015.gif)

15. Wayu<u>ta</u>fu AAalayhim bi-<u>a</u>niyatin min fi<u>dd</u>atin
waakw<u>a</u>bin k<u>a</u>nat qaw<u>a</u>reer<u>a</u>

15\. And amongst them will be  
Passed round vessels of silver  
And goblets of crystal,—

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/076/076_016.gif)

16. Qaw<u>a</u>reera min fi<u>dd</u>atin qaddarooh<u>a</u>
taqdeer<u>a</u>**n**

16\. Crystal-clear, made of silver:  
They will determine  
The measure thereof  
(According to their wishes).

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/076/076_017.gif)

17. Wayusqawna feeh<u>a</u> ka/san k<u>a</u>na miz<u>a</u>juh<u>a</u>
zanjabeel<u>a</u>**n**

17\. And they will be given  
To drink there of a Cup  
(Of Wine) mixed  
With Zanjaḅīl,—

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/076/076_018.gif)

18. AAaynan feeh<u>a</u> tusamm<u>a</u> salsabeel<u>a</u>**n**

18\. A fountain there,  
Called Salsabīl.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/076/076_019.gif)

19. Waya<u>t</u>oofu AAalayhim wild<u>a</u>nun mukhalladoona i<u>tha</u>
raaytahum <u>h</u>asibtahum lu/lu-an manthoor<u>a</u>**n**

19\. And round about them  
Will (serve) youths  
Of perpetual (freshness):  
If thou seest them,  
Thou wouldst think them  
Scattered Pearls.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/076/076_020.gif)

20. Wa-i<u>tha</u> raayta thamma raayta naAAeeman wamulkan
kabeer<u>a</u>**n**

20\. And when thou lookest,  
It is there thou wilt see  
A Bliss and  
A Realm Magnificent.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/076/076_021.gif)

21. AA<u>a</u>liyahum thiy<u>a</u>bu sundusin khu<u>d</u>run
wa-istabraqun wa<u>h</u>ulloo as<u>a</u>wira min fi<u>dd</u>atin
wasaq<u>a</u>hum rabbuhum shar<u>a</u>ban <u>t</u>ahoor<u>a</u>**n**

21\. Upon them will be  
Green Garments of fine silk  
And heavy brocade,  
And they will be adorned  
With Bracelets of silver;  
And their Lord will  
Give to them to drink  
Of a Wine  
Pure and Holy.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/076/076_022.gif)

22. Inna h<u>atha</u> k<u>a</u>na lakum jaz<u>a</u>an wak<u>a</u>na
saAAyukum mashkoor<u>a</u>**n**

22\. "Verily this is a Reward  
For you, and your Endeavour  
Is accepted and recognised."

